      "explanation": "A ratio is a comparison of two quantities of the same kind, so units cancel out.",
      "frequencyRating": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "g7_m7_q3",
      "text": "If two ratios are equal, they are said to be in:",
      "options": ["Addition", "Subtraction", "Proportion", "Fraction"],
      "correctIndex": 2,
      "explanation": "Equality of two ratios is called proportion.",
      "frequencyRating": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "g7_m7_q4",
      "text": "The word 'percent' comes from the Latin word 'per centum' which means:",
